text: Sir Edwin Landseer (1802–1873) was a British painter. Landseer may also refer to: * Landseer (dog), a black-and-white variant of the Newfoundland, named after the painter * Landseer (horse) (1999–2002), thoroughbred racehorse trained in Ireland == People with the surname == * Albert Henry Landseer (1829–1906), South Australian politician and businessman * Charles Landseer (1799–1879), English painter * Jessica Landseer (1810–1880), English landscape and miniature painter * John Landseer (1769–1852), English landscape engraver * Thomas Landseer (c.1793–1880), English artist ==See also== * Landseer Park, Suffolk, England * Landser (disambiguation)
title: Landseer (disambiguation)
